APPLE IIe

•	What year was it made?
1983

•	What operating system does it run? 
Apple DOS 3.3

•	How much did it cost (then and now, adjusted for inflation)? How hard is it to find one on the secondhand market (check eBay and Craig’s List).
Then: $1,298.00; $2,841.73-adjusted for inflation
Now: the best model (or model I'd most trust) on ebay is $359.00 but there are some that range lower ($159-$250)

•	In brief (a short paragraph), what were its historical strengths and weaknesses as a platform? What was it best known for?
The Apple IIe was praised for its improvements to the Apple II, while remaining capatible with earlier models. According to Wikipedia, this model was available for 

over ten years (from January 1983 to November 1993), which if true, is a testament to its usefulness. Its easy to use functions made it desirable for first-time 

computer owners. 


Turn it on (you must figure out how). Work your way through the Apple Presents Apple tutorial. Try a game or two. (If you can beat one of my high scores on Sea Dragon 

you’ll get a prize. Really!)

~#there is both a switch in front and a switch in back to turn it on
~#I had problems with the monitor jumping, blurring, and cutting out on me. I e-mailed you about it. I tried to do as much as the tutorial as I could manage to 

decipher, but in the end, it just gave me a headache.

