MACINTOSH SE

•	What year was it made?
1989

•	What operating system does it run? 
The manuel says "Macintosh Operating System" on page 30

•	How much did it cost (then and now, adjusted for inflation)? How hard is it to find one on the secondhand market (check eBay and Craig’s List). 
Then: $6,495.00; $11,421.56-adjusted for inflation
Now: There are quite a few on ebay that range from $15-$95.

•	In brief (a short paragraph), what were its historical strengths and weaknesses as a platform? What was it best known for?
Fun fact: first Macintosh unit to have an internal cooling fan, a feature in computers many of us take for granted. Like most of the other computers, this was 

historical best as a personal computer. From the story elements, this was probably a good computer for primary and secondary schools. While it has decent specs, the 

price tag seems a little steep for what was available in 1989.


Turn it on (you must figure out how). Read some of Deena Larsen’s Marble Springs. Quit Marble Springs. What else is on this Mac?
