AMIGA

•	What year was it made? 
1985

•	What operating system does it run?
Amiga OS

•	How much did it cost (then and now, adjusted for inflation)? How hard is it to find one on the secondhand market (check eBay and Craig’s List).
Then: $1,295.00; $2,624.37-adjusted for inflation
Now: after scouring E-bay, I found a full model for $550.00
 
•	In brief (a short paragraph), what were its historical strengths and weaknesses as a platform? What was it best known for?
It was best known for being a great home desktop, because of its creative software. This computer was by far the most colorful and you can tell in the demos the 

developers put a lot into the design. The weakness in the Amiga was apparently it could not keep up with the improvements of other systems and fell to the wayside.

Turn it on (you must figure out how). Try the demos. What else can it do? (Hint: try the “Amiga Appetizer” disk). Have a look at the Amiga magazines and the book, The 

Future Was Here.
